Class SVGRenderer

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
Constants, java.awt.print.Printable, Renderer
public class SVGRenderer
extends Java2DRenderer

This renderer generates SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics) format.

This class actually does not render itself, instead it extends org.apache.fop.render.java2D.Java2DRenderer and uses Apache Batik's SVGGraphics2D for SVG generation.

renderPage

public void renderPage(PageViewport pageViewport)
                throws java.io.IOException
Description copied from class: Java2DRenderer
This method override only stores the PageViewport in a List. No actual rendering is performed here. A renderer override renderPage() to get the freshly produced PageViewport, and rendere them on the fly (producing the desired BufferedImages by calling getPageImage(), which lazily starts the rendering process).

Specified by:
